The paper deals with the problem of Locality Sensitive Hashing (LSH) in high-dimensional spaces, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The paper focuses on the Hamming distance, which is a discrete metric, and provides an optimal lower bound for the rho parameter, which is a measure of the quality of LSH families. This suggests that the paper belongs to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. However, the paper also uses techniques from information theory (cs.IT), computational complexity (cs.CC), computational geometry (cs.CG), and discrete mathematics (cs.DM) to prove the lower bound. Therefore, these sub-categories are also likely candidates.
